items.title: Kirloskar firms challenge SEBI letter asking disclosure of family settlement deed at SAT
items.description: Kirloskar siblings, with Sanjay (Kirloskar Brothers Ltd Chairman and Managing Director) on one side and Atul and Rahul on the other, have been in a feud since 2016 over the DFS for the assets of the more than 130-year-old Kirloskar group.

items.title: Committed to turning Air India into top-class airline in the world, says N Chandrasekaran
items.description: The Tata Group took complete control of Air India from the government, nearly 69 years after it was taken from the conglomerate.

items.title: HDFC Bank says Q3 deposit growth outpaces loan growth
items.description: HDFC Bank has the most assets among all private banks in India. It merged with its parent HDFC in July 2023, adding a large pool of loans to its portfolio but a much smaller volume of deposits.
